            "container_id": "cntr_69d55e5b11dc8190b29e277eab1ee31e06857dfcb0e37628",
            "code": "import numpy as np\nfrom scipy.optimize import fsolve\n\n# Define the equation as a function\ndef equation(x):\n    return np.sin(x) + x**2 - 42\n\n# We'll start our guesses from both the positive and negative side\ninitial_guesses = [6, -6] \n\n# Find solutions\nsolutions = [fsolve(equation, guess)[0] for guess in initial_guesses]\n\n# Remove duplicate (in case the equation only has one root)\nsolutions = list(set(np.round(solutions, 6)))\n\nsolutions",
